Package api.dataAccess

Interface DataAccessInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
DataAccess
public interface DataAccessInterface
Represents all the functions that can be called on the database. For the most part, functions are CRUD operations: Create, Read, Update, Delete

  • Method Details

    • clear

      void clear() throws DataAccessException
      Clears all stored data in the database: users, games, authTokens. Will not be available outside of testing.
      Throws:
      DataAccessException - Throws an error if it's not able to clear the database for some reason.

    • createUser

      UserData createUser(UserData user)
      Creates a new user and stores it in the database. If the user or username already exist, don't add them again.
      Parameters:
      user - The new user's data (As a UserData object).
      Returns:
      The new UserData object.

    • findUser

      UserData findUser(String username)
      Gets a user from the database and returns it.
      Parameters:
      username - The username we're looking for.
      Returns:
      The UserData object if found in the database, returns null if not found.

    • updateUser

      UserData updateUser(UserData user) throws DataAccessException
      Updates a user's information in the database.
      Parameters:
      user - The user's updated information (As a UserData object).
      Returns:
      The updated UserData object.
      Throws:
      DataAccessException - Throws an error if not able to perform operation.

    • deleteUser

      void deleteUser(UserData user) throws DataAccessException
      Deletes a user from the database.
      Parameters:
      user - The UserData object to be updated.
      Throws:
      DataAccessException - Throws an error if not possible to delete
